lity as Valis I saw Brahman, + in me: atmans but is Tagore real? I think so he may be the conjurer: I have seen him at last t + it is Lord Krishna, as I have long suspected. Here is the point: all questions of epistemology aside, Tagore is what t La) man can become, + this is real. Tagore represents man perfected, at his absolute fulfillment. Which has nothing to do with \"Ti to on?\" or maybe it does; maybe Tagore is the answer to that question. but I stick with my insight of last night 2-3-74 is Xtian magic (due to my belief-absolute pistic) + does not verify Xtianity but rather Sankara's Buddha's doctrina of maya as stul + This realization is very sophisticated: because by the very nature of Maya it (it magy + it the situation) would seem to confirm Xtianity. + this realization has totally eluded me for - years + since Tagore is what man perfected becomes I reason Tagore is the Buddha + not Krishna) It is almost as if due to a flure (2-74) combination of circum‐ stances I tricked maya or it tricked itself: it was in a no-win situation -90 I Now, there is an internal consis fency between Tagore being, the Buddha, my 2-3-74 experience of + with Maya, + my realizing that it is Maya, for the concept of \"Maya is central to Buddhism moreover, the term \"Buddha\" would refer to someone who had become awakened + this precisely is what is Seing Maya (world) for what it involves. Thus to see maya (reality as \"sillyputty\") but fail to identify it as maya - this stops short of full enlightenment (awakening); but to (1) see it as Maya (2-3-74) + then (2) to realize this - this is the awakerying that basically characterizes the Buddha's understanding of reality. This dreaming about Tagore is a crucial clue to what 2-3-74 was really all about - if I realize that Tagore is Buddha, + I have reasoned this to my satisfaction - + then I see how it goes back + throws crucial light on 2-3-74 as a conjurer's trick (rope seen as snade). So the Tagore dream is the crucial crue that explains the whole bule of way If I perceive Tagore as Buddha - + as e C-91 Now, this is in full accord with the radical epistemology of my 10 volume meta-novel, but the Xtianity is true\" theory is not I'm onto something here. The Tagore dream is quintessential. Everything must be understood in terms of it. A new epistemology may -in con‐ junction with his birth - have come into existence: This is then, a new epoch. No earlier model of reality may apply. on the other hand the birth of the new savior would be accompanied by vast dis‐ ruptions in the normal order of things. One must work backward from the incarnation for It is the point of the whole thing, in terms of which otherwise inexplicable events when seen in context make sense. We can no more figure out the broad epistemological-mystical situation than we could, before hearing the Kerygma, infer It (the moral/ethical system). After all, a whole planet is being extricated from its fate (by way of divine intervention). I suddenly did a \"make\" on that vision of the slit-like wound in in thigh: it looked like (I have been thinking) like an often-shown color photo brought back by voyager; or II Saturn? +thought of Dythrambis born a second time from Zeus' thigh. Sud e denly I realized: the probe photo is of the red spot on supiter. Jupiter-Zeus. Dythrambus-Zagreus-Christ - the spear a wound on the cross. This wound in my thigh refers to the birth of the C-92 savior (Dythrambus-Zagreus) + the death (crucifixion of Christ). Strange Tagore is born; the savior is here as but also already he is wounded Christ was at his death as if the birth + death of the savior are now (this time) one single event; he is simultaneously coming to us + leaving us, rather than first being born + later dying. Thus in a sense that I do not understand, his wounds give birth -like a vagina - or are associated wits birth. His death is life-giving: of course: to the ecosphere, since he accepts (vicarious atonement) its wounds on his body + so 